OL,3,CPolitician who 'let down' Jersey
OL,4,Cpeople avoids jail despite immigration
OL,5,Coffences
OL,7,FOzouf, 55, who first became a States
OL,8,Fmember in 1999 and held government
OL,9,Fpositions including Minister for
OL,10,FExternal Relations, had applied for
OL,11,Fhis own work permits for staff at his
OL,12,Flaundry but had been refused.
OL,14,FHe then did a deal with Roberto Lora,
OL,15,Fthe owner of the Savoy hotel in St
OL,16,FHelier, who has obtained permits for
OL,17,Ffour of the Rwandan nationals to work
OL,18,Ffor him in hospitality. The fifth was
OL,19,Fnot employed at the hotel.
