OL,4,Cpeople avoids jail despite immigration
OL,5,Coffences
OL,7,FThe court heard Ozouf employed the
OL,8,Ffive workers to work part time or full
OL,9,Ftime at his laundry business and at
OL,10,Fhis home, but he never issued them
OL,11,Fwith a contract.
OL,13,FOzouf benefited from this arrangement
OL,14,Fas he employed them on 'relatively low
OL,15,Fwages' for work they were not allowed
OL,16,Fto do.
